ility to service debt and obtain financing. However, it should be noted that Adjusted Homebuilding EBITDA is not a U.S. generally accepted accounting principles (&#8220;GAAP&#8221;) financial measure. Due to the significance of the GAAP components excluded, Adjusted Homebuilding EBITDA should not be considered in isolation or as an alternative to cash flows from operations or any other liquidity performance measure prescribed by GAAP.</font></div>\n</td>\n</tr></table>\n</div>\n\n<div style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt\" align=\"left\"><font style=\"DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt\"><br>\n</font></div>\n\n<div style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt\" align=\"left\"><font style=\"DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt\"><br>\n</font></div>\n\n<div style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt\" align=\"left\"><font style=\"DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt\"><br>\n</font></div>\n\n<div style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt\" align=\"left\">\n<div id=\"PGBRK\" style=\"TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; WIDTH: 100%; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt\">\n<div id=\"FTR\">\n<div id=\"GLFTR\" style=\"WIDTH: 100%\" align=\"center\"><font style=\"DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 8pt\">&#160; </font></div>\n</div>\n\n<div id=\"PN\" style=\"PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always; WIDTH: 100%\">\n<div style=\"TEXT-ALIGN: center; WIDTH: 100%\"><font style=\"DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt\">18</font></div>\n\n<div style=\"TEXT-ALIGN: center; WIDTH: 100%\">\n<hr style=\"COLOR: black\" noshade size=\"2\">\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div id=\"HDR\">\n<div id=\"GLHDR\" style=\"WIDTH: 100%\" align=\"left\"><font style=\"DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 9pt\"><a href=\"#tableofcontents\">Table of Contents</a